							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/melissalozadaoliva/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Melissa-Lozada-Oliva_Photo-credit-Chimera-Singer-e1717774939518-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Melissa Lozada-Oliva" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/melissalozadaoliva/">Melissa Lozada-Oliva</a></h6>
										Melissa Lozada-Oliva is the child of Guatemalan and Colombian immigrants and the author of <em>Dreaming of You</em>, <em>Candelaria</em>, and <em>peluda</em>. Her work has been featured in <em>NPR</em>, <em>Vogue</em>, <em>Harper’s Bazaar</em>, <em>PAPER</em>, <em>Armani Beauty</em>, and more. She is a member of the band Meli and the Specs. She holds an MFA in poetry from NYU and lives in New York City.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
